    "benefits": "Codonoboea lilacina is reported to have several health benefits, primarily due to its rich content of antioxidants and flavonoids. The plant's extracts have been found to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which may contribute to its potential health benefits. It is also believed to have antioxidant and free radical scavenging activities, which can help protect against cell damage and oxidative stress. Additionally, some studies suggest that Codonoboea lilacina may have anti-cancer and anti-diabetic properties, although more research is needed to confirm these findings. Further investigation is necessary to fully understand the potential health benefits of Codonoboea lilacina.",
